						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in the Lakshmīnārāyaṇa temple.</p>						

						<p>Bhillama, 1189 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the 3rd regnal year of the king, Saumya, Pushya ba. 1, Monday, Uttarāyaṇa-saṁkrānti, corresponding to 1189 A.D., December 25.</p>						

						<p>It registers the gift of the village Bivavura to the god Lakshmī-Narasiṁha whose temple was built by Chauḍiseṭṭi, grandfather of Śaṅkara-svāmi. The gift was made by the king at the request of <hi rend="italic">Paṭṭa-sāhaṇādhipati</hi> Pēyiya and his subordinate Malleya.</p>						

						<p>Published in the <hi rend="italic">Epigraphia Indica.,</hi> Vol. XV, pp. 30 ff.</p>						

						</summary>
